<div id="banner">
	<h1>secroll</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p><a href="../2002/secroll.py">secroll</a> is a python program to allow you to securely roll an n-sided die between two parties. If you remember <a href="000218">secure coin flipping</a>, this is a generalization of that.</p>

<p>If you have expertise in the area, I&#8217;d really appreciate it if you could review it and let me know what you think. I&#8217;m especially interested in hearing about bugs and security holes. Thanks! <!-- I'm not certain it's bugfree or secure. If I was Knuth, I'd offer $0.32 for each bug and $2.56 for each security hole. Actually, if I really was Knuth I'd offer $2.56 for each bug and $20.48 for each bug. If I was D. J. Bernstein, I'd offer $100 for each security hole. Maybe I will after a couple people have reviewed it. --></p>

